The paper deals with simulation games played on automata, which are typically studied in the areas of logic (cs.LO) and formal languages (cs.FL). The paper also discusses decidability and complexity, which are topics studied in the areas of data structures (cs.DS) and computational complexity (cs.CC). Finally, the paper mentions sufficient conditions for winning the game, which could be related to programming languages (cs.PL).
